        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:16PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Columbus, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Adger and Mill Spring.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
